manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Features Transfer speed, transfer performance Transcend's SSD220 provides an incredible 4K random read and write performance of up to 280MB/s, making it the perfect alternative as a boot disk to load your everyday computing tasks and programs in just seconds. Taking full advantage of the SATA III 6Gb/s interface and built in with SLC caching technology, the SSD220 achieves exceptional transfer speeds of up to 540MB/s read and 500MB/s write. Endurance. Reliability. In addition to blazing-fast transfer speeds, the SSD220 is engineered with a RAID engine and LDPC (Low-Density Parity Check) coding, a powerful ECC algorithm, in order to keep your data secure. Built-in wear-leveling technology ensures data integrity during transmission, prolonging the lifespan of Transcend's SSD220. Save power, save time With full support of SATA Device Sleep Mode (DevSleep), the SSD220 can prolong notebook battery life by intelligently shutting down the SATA interface when it is not in use. DevSleep features an ultra-low power state to conserve battery power. With a remarkable response time of less than 20 milliseconds, you can get back to work instantaneously.

Features Take control with SSD Scope To keep your Transcend SSD running fast and error-free, Transcend's advanced SSD Scope software application is available for download for use with the SSD220. Monitor your SSD's health status with S.M.A.R.T. technology, enable the TRIM command for optimum write speeds, keep your SSD's firmware up-to-date, and migrate data from your original drive to a new SSD with just a few clicks. Ultra-slim, ultra-portable To The SSD220 features an industry-standard 2.5" form factor. Yet, it measures just 6.8mm in height and only weighs a mere 45g, which is best suited for ultra-thin computing devices such as Ultrabooks, in addition to mainstream PCs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 28, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good product ... good price ...
reviews.reviewText: While it's not the fastest or the cheapest among the SSDs, it is still way faster than any conventional HD, even the 7,200 RPM models. I chose the 480GB unit over 512GB model because it was significantly cheaper.I cringe whenever people move about with the laptop in their hands while it's on and not in sleep or off mode. A sure way to potentially damage the HD. One of the main advantages of SSD besides the increased speed is no moving parts, thus it gives you the freedom to lug the laptop around without damaging it while it's on. When you've gone SSD, it's hard to go back to using conventional HD. I must have over dozen laptop HDs sitting in the drawer, merely serving as a backup drive in case SSD crashes and burns. I have installed about two dozen SSDs in laptops past four years. Luckily, none have failed thus far. I keep the original HDs because SSDs can and do fail from time to time.This 480 GB Transcend unit is performing admirably thus far in a Dell unit. I've used couple other Transcend SSDs in the past without any problems.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 12, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great performance, seems reliable, avoid using bundled software for imaging
reviews.reviewText: The physical installation was easy as are most SSDs.I used this to replace an old 120gb intel ssd as my main drive for Windows. The SSD Scope software included from transcend failed to image my old drive correctly and I had to manually install windows and all of my software. After that, everything worked perfectly.Performance is excellent for the price point of this drive (got it for $70ish for 480gb version on black Friday).So far been using for 6 months with zero issues, no studders, lockups and very fast load times for games like Forza Horizon 3, Witcher 3 and others.Very happy with purchase! Avoid relying on SSD scope to image your old drive!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Transcend SSD will transform your computer
reviews.reviewText: This SSD met all expectations. It was easy to install. Make sure to download the Transcend SSD Scope software. I used the clone tool and it copied my C: drive and OS system and programs on to the SSD. It took about three hours.After moving the SSD into the boot slot the computer started up fast and without issue. Every start up since then has been amazingly fast. Formerly slow programs (like Photoshop) now come up in a fraction of the time they used to take. The delay is almost none existence.

reviews.reviewText: Got it on a New Years special. Great drive for the price. I'm getting the posted speeds which is a major plus. Put into a new PC and installed windows from USB in under a minute. Can't speak to the life of the drive as I've only used it a short time. Wish I could get some M2 storage.Core i5 6600KMSI Krait Gaming 3x MoboMSI 1070 Gaming X 8GB16GB GaiL RAM

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Fast enough for what I need
reviews.reviewText: I have been buying Transcend disks for several years now, solid state, flash memory and spinners. I have found them to be reliable, less expensive than the big name brands, but also somewhat slower, so I buy them when speed is not that important to me. When speed is important I usually buy Samsung, but expect to pay a noticeable premium for that extra speed.I bought this drive as an external usb3 drive for a MacBook Air and enclosed it in a UASP optimized enclosure to use it to store digital photos when I travel. I have run speed tests on it and confirmed that it is somewhat slower (about 25% for writing, about the same for reading) than a similar Samsung SSD that I use on my main desktop for photo processing, but fast enough for what I want to do, and considerably less expensive than the Samsung. I have not noticed any of my Transcend drives becoming hot when used and, being solid state, they can be moved even when data is being written to or read from them.I use Transcend products in my digital camera, as auxiliary memory (the Transcend JetDrive) in my MacBook Pro and now as added memory to my traveling laptop and have never had an issue with any of the Transcend products. As I mentioned, they are not as fast as some of the more expensive products, but fast enough for use when the load is not too heavy and speed is not that important.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great bang for the buck!
reviews.reviewText: Transcend has been in the SSD game since it started! I work as a computer repair/upgrade tech from home and I have been pleasantly surprised by the quality and speed of Transcend SSD drives.In the past 18 months I have replaced 5 or 6 old laptop and desktop hard drives with these SSD drives.Their reliability rating rivals Samsung for a fraction of the price. Speed tests usually show 550MBps read and 400+MBps write. Most laptop drives have a hard time pushing anything over 100MBps read and write.This helps for fast boot times and quicker launching programs. I have replaced these drives on everything from a low-end AMD E3 processor to an Intel Core i7. Obviously the better the processor the quicker the system.I have had zero problems or failures of these drives to date.I highly recommend this product!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 14, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The working life of my workstation has just doubled!
reviews.reviewText: Bought this drive on sale through Amazon, great deal. It went into an older but still very usable Gateway Core i7 desktop, 8GB RAM that is used for CS4 programs, mostly Photoshop and Premiere Pro. Cloned 290GB of system drive and data from a 1TB 7200 RPM Barracuda using the free version of EaseUs. Boot time dropped from 3 - 5 minutes to about 30 seconds, and program opening times are slashed. This computer is almost 5 years old and barring any major failures may well be usable for another 5. It's a better workstation than it was when it was new. Photoshop editing is quicker than any hardware I've ever worked on. I have yet to render video, but expect those times to be a third or less than in the past. I'm very pleased, this is my best computer technology purchase in years.
